HEADWORD: emmer
<hw>emmer</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a hard red wheat (<spn>Triticum
dicoccum</spn>) grown especially in Russia and Germany; also grown in
the U. S. as stock feed.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> starch wheat, two-grain spelt, <spn>Triticum
dicoccum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
